<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7402> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7402" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A senator named in the SC de Thisbensibus (SIG(3) 646-Sherk, RDGE no. 2, 26-31). Mommsen suggested that the mention of his tribe was a means of distinguishing him from the leading branch of the Acilii, the Glabriones (EE 1.288; see no. 36). He should be attributed to the Balbi, one of whom was consul in 150. (See L. R. Taylor, VDRR 185-186.)\n" .
